# RUBLI — Mexican Government Procurement Analysis Platform
# Cursor AI context — read before every inline edit and chat response.

## What this project is
Full-stack corruption detection platform analyzing 3.1M federal procurement contracts
(2002–2025). FastAPI backend + React/TypeScript frontend + SQLite.

Backend port: 8001 | Frontend port: 3009

---

## Critical rules (NEVER violate these)

### Python
- Python 3.11 — NO backslashes inside f-string expressions. Use intermediate variables:
  BAD:  f"{x\n}"
  GOOD: val = x\n; f"{val}"
- ALWAYS use parameterized queries, never string interpolation:
  GOOD: cursor.execute("SELECT * FROM contracts WHERE id = ?", (contract_id,))
  BAD:  cursor.execute(f"SELECT * FROM contracts WHERE id = {contract_id}")
- Database connection pattern: `with get_db() as conn:` — NOT `conn = get_db()`.
  get_db() is a @contextmanager — calling without `with` returns a generator silently.
- FastAPI route ordering: static paths BEFORE parameterized paths.
  `/contracts/export` must come before `/contracts/{id}` or the wrong handler fires.

### TypeScript
- After any .ts/.tsx change, BOTH must pass with 0 errors:
  npx tsc --noEmit          ← lenient tsconfig.json
  npm run build             ← strict tsconfig.app.json (noUnusedLocals, noUnusedParameters)
- Remove all unused imports and variables before finishing.

### Amount validation (MEMORIZE)
| Value         | Action                    |
|---------------|---------------------------|
| > 100B MXN    | REJECT — decimal error    |
| > 10B MXN     | FLAG — include but mark   |
| <= 10B MXN    | Accept normally           |

---

## Architecture

```
backend/
  api/
    routers/      ← FastAPI route handlers (thin — delegate to services)
    services/     ← Business logic, DB queries
    main.py       ← App entry point, startup checks (30-60s cold start, normal)
  scripts/        ← ETL pipeline, risk model training
  RUBLI_NORMALIZED.db  ← SQLite, ~5.6GB, 3.1M contracts

frontend/
  src/
    pages/        ← 36 page components (lazy-loaded)
    components/   ← Shared UI (shadcn/ui base + custom)
    components/ui/← Primitive UI: AnimatedCounter, RiskScoreBar, RiskLevelPill, StatCard
    lib/api.ts    ← Typed API client (all fetch calls go here)
    lib/constants.ts ← Risk thresholds, sector colors, shared constants
    i18n/locales/ ← en/ and es/ JSON files, one per page namespace
    hooks/        ← Custom React hooks
```

## Database schema (key columns)

contracts table:
  id, vendor_id, institution_id, sector_id, year, amount_mxn,
  risk_score, risk_level (critical/high/medium/low),
  risk_confidence_lower, risk_confidence_upper,
  is_single_bid, is_direct_award, is_year_end,
  risk_model_version ('v5.0' tag in model_calibration, active = v5.1)

Risk levels: critical >= 0.50 | high >= 0.30 | medium >= 0.10 | low < 0.10
(defined in frontend/src/lib/constants.ts)

---

## Risk model v5.1 (ACTIVE)

- 16 z-score features, 12 per-sector logistic regressions + 1 global fallback
- Elkan & Noto PU-learning correction (c = 0.882)
- Train AUC: 0.964 | Test AUC: 0.957 (temporal split — train ≤2020, test ≥2021)
- High-risk rate: 9.0% (OECD benchmark: 2-15%)
- Scores are risk indicators, not corruption probabilities — use for triage, not verdicts

Top predictors: price_volatility (+1.22), institution_diversity (-0.85), win_rate (+0.73)

